  "text": "In our simulations, we used γ = 2.9, which we extracted from the Porto Downtown dataset for the NLOSb conditions where there were no significant single-interaction reflections/diffractions. Previous studies reported similar values: γ = 2.9 by Durgin et. al. [CITATION_1] (NLOSb environment) and 2.44 ≤ γ ≤ 3.39 by Paschalidis et al. [CITATION_2] (urban environment -various (N)LOS conditions).",
